Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the challenges and approaches for improving the end-to-end latency of cellular networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes techniques for error control coding and signal processing to reduce latency, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions enhanced mobile broadband applications, which are related to multimedia. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper briefly discusses security concerns related to mission critical applications. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses network design approaches for latency reduction, which can be related to systems and control.
